Another form of the aggregation relationship, but the child class’s instance lifecycle is dependent on the parent class’s instance lifecycle. Composition implies a relationship where the child cannot exist independent of the parent: WeeklySchedule is composed in Flight which means when Flight lifecycle ends, WeeklySchedule automatically gets destroyed.
